id: jf-rjox
title: Fallback to the exact official Jellyfin OpenAPI document
description: "A transient HTTP 500 from the local Jellyfin 10.11.11 OpenAPI route exposed a resilience gap. Prefer the local document, but resolve and validate an exact official stable document without forwarding credentials when every local candidate is unavailable; cache only below the private CLI data directory and report provenance."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: api,openapi,resilience,security
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:00:05.640Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:26.376Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:25.501Z"
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "Local candidates remain preferred; Fallback resolves an exact safe semantic server version from /System/Info/Public; No authentication header is sent to repo.jellyfin.org; Cache is private, versioned, validated, and reusable offline; Doctor, setup validate, schema research, and schema coverage pass against the local 10.11.11 instance"
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Restore live API research and readiness diagnostics on current Jellyfin.
impact: Agents can inspect the actual server contract even when server-hosted Swagger generation fails.
outcome: Exact-version official fallback with explicit source and cache provenance.
why_now: Live readiness currently fails solely because the server OpenAPI route returns HTTP 500.
parent: jf-gn5j
reviewer: maintainer
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
severity: high
environment: Jellyfin 10.11.11 at a private local URL; jf-cli 2026.7.21-3
repro_steps: "Temporarily make all local OpenAPI candidates unavailable, then run schema or doctor diagnostics; the resolver must fall back safely. Repeated current probes of /api-docs/openapi.json return 356 paths and 429 operations."
resolution: Local-first discovery now falls back only to a version-matched official or private cached document and exposes its source.
expected_result: Schema diagnostics remain available safely when local OpenAPI endpoints fail.
actual_result: "Twenty-four resolver tests pass, including local preference, credential isolation, 0600 cache files, cache reuse, and version-mismatch rejection; current live local discovery returns 429 operations."
component: schema-research
customer_impact: "Schema discovery, coverage analysis, and setup readiness gates fail for agents despite an otherwise healthy server."
